29/05/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- The Turkish Red Crescent announced on Sunday (28 May) it will donate $100,000 in emergency funds to Indonesia, for relief efforts following the deadly earthquake on the island of Java, which killed more than 4,500 people and injured thousands more. 
A Turkish relief team has been in Indonesia since the 2004 tsunami disaster.
Also Saturday, Greece said it is sending 200,000 euros to help the humanitarian effort under way in Indonesia. 
More funds could be available after monitoring the situation on the ground, the foreign ministry added. 
(Kathimerini - 29/05/06; NTV, Turkishpress.com, Anadolu Agency - 28/05/06)
